<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 10:56PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Dallam
County through 1130 PM CDT...
At 1056 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Sedan, or 21 miles northeast of Amistad, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of western Dallam
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
